Kim Jong Il Meets Senior Official of CPC 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 30 (KCNA) -- General Secretary Kim Jong Il on Tuesday received Liu Yunshan, member of the Political Bureau and member of the Secretariat and head of the Publicity Department of the Central Committee of the Communist Party of China, and his entourage on a visit to the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On the occasion, Liu Yunshan conveyed a verbal personal message from Hu Jintao, General Secretary of the CPC Central Committee, to General Secretary Kim Jong Il and informed him of the results of the 17th Congress of the CPC upon the authorization. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Jong Il thanked for this and congratulated the CPC on the success of its congress before having a cordial and friendly talk with Liu. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He gave a luncheon for the guests. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there on invitation were Liu and his entourage and Chinese Ambassador to the DPRK Liu Xiaoming. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Also on hand were First Vice-Minister of Foreign Affairs Kang Sok Ju, Department Director of the WPK Central Committee Kim Yang Gon, and Vice Department Directors of the C.C., WPK Ji Jae Ryong and Pak Kyong Son. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The luncheon proceeded in a cordial atmosphere overflowing with friendship. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Liu presented Kim Jong Il with a gift.

Chinese Guest Feted 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 30 (KCNA) -- The Central Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea hosted a reception in honor of Liu Yunshan, member of the Political Bureau and member of the Secretariat and head of the Publicity Department of the Central Committee of the Communist Party of China, on a visit to the DPRK, on Monday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there on invitation were Liu Yunshan's party and Ambassador Liu Xiaoming and staff members of the Chinese embassy here. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there were Choe Thae Bok, alternate Politburo member and secretary of the WPK Central Committee, Pak Kyong Son, vice department director of the C.C., the WPK, and officials concerned. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Speaking at the reception, Choe Thae Bok hoped that the Chinese people would register fresh successes in the work to implement the tasks laid down at the 17th Congress of the CPC under the guidance of the Party with Hu Jintao as its General Secretary. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Liu Yunshan in a speech wished the Korean party and people bigger achievements in building a great prosperous powerful nation.

Chinese Guest Visits Friendship Tower 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 30 (KCNA) -- Liu Yunshan, member of the Political Bureau and member of the Secretariat and head of the Publicity Department of the Central Committee of the Communist Party of China, and his party on a visit to the DPRK visited the Friendship Tower on Tuesday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They were accompanied by Kwon Hyok Bong and Pak Kyong Son, vice department directors of the Central Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea, officials concerned and Ambassador Liu Xiaoming and staff members of the Chinese embassy here. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A wreath in name of Liu Yunshan was laid before the tower. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The visitors paid a silent tribute to the fallen fighters of the Chinese People's Volunteers who fought in the Korean war. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Liu wrote in the visitor's book that the peoples of the two countries defended peace shoulder to shoulder with each other and would build future together.

Premier Kim Yong Il Pays Courtesy Call on Vietnamese President 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Hanoi, October 29 (KCNA Correspondent) -- Kim Yong Il, premier of the DPRK Cabinet, paid a courtesy call on Nguyen Minh Triet, President of Vietnam, on Oct. 29 at the Presidency. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A conversation was held between them in a friendly atmosphere. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there were Rim Kyong Man, minister of Foreign Trade, Ri Kyong Sik, minister of Agriculture, Mun Jae Chol, acting chairman of the Korean Committee for Cultural Relations with Foreign Countries, Kim Yong Il, vice-minister of Foreign Affairs, and Ma Chol Su, DPRK ambassador to Vietnam. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Also on hand were Nguyen Hoo Luc, deputy chief of the General Office of the Presidency, Nguyen Van Tho, deputy minister of Foreign Affairs, Do Xuan Dong, assistant to the president, and Le Van Cu, Vietnamese ambassador to the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On the same day the premier of the DPRK and his party visited an office in Hanoi where President Ho Chi Minh worked. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They also inspected Nui Bao Coal Mine, Ha Long Bay, Hai Phong Port and other places.

Congratulations to Great King of Cambodia 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 30 (KCNA) -- Kim Yong Nam, president of the Presidium of the DPRK Supreme People's Assembly, Monday sent a congratulatory message to Norodom Sihanouk, Great King of Cambodia, on the occasion of his 85th birthday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The message noted that the great king is deeply respected and loved by all the Cambodian people as he has devoted all his life to the independence of Cambodia, unity of the Khmers and happiness of the people and performed great feats for the country and the nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean people express high respects to you who are doing your best to develop the friendly relations between the two countries, valuing the ties of fraternal obligation with President Kim Il Sung, it said. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The message wholeheartedly wished the great king, a close friend of the Korean people, happiness in good health and greater success in the patriotic cause for stability and prosperity of the country.

Greetings to President of Turkey 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 30 (KCNA) -- Kim Yong Nam, president of the Presidium of the DPRK Supreme People's Assembly, sent a message of greetings to Abdulah Gul, President of Turkey, on Oct. 29 on the occasion of its national day. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Expressing the belief that the relations between the DPRK and Turkey would grow stronger in the mutual interests, the message wholeheartedly wished the president success in his responsible work for the stability and prosperity of the country.

DPRK Foreign Minister Meets Swiss Ambassador 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 30 (KCNA) -- DPRK Foreign Minister Pak Ui Chun met and had a conversation with Dante Martineli, Swiss ambassador to the DPRK who paid a courtesy call on him, on Monday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there were officials concerned, a staff member of the Swiss embassy and the country director of the Swiss Cooperation Office of the DPRK of the Federal Department of Foreign Affairs.

Visits 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 30 (KCNA) -- A delegation of the Workers' Party of Korea led by Kong Pyong Gil, vice department director of its Central Committee, left Pyongyang today to visit Russia and Belarus. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Arriving here today was a delegation of the China Classification Society led by its Vice-President Sun Licheng and a delegation of the All-China Federation of Trade Unions led by Member of the Secretariat Zhang Qiu Jian.

S. Korean Visitors Here
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 30 (KCNA) -- President of the Red Cross of south Korea Han Wan Sang and his party arrived here today. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Also arriving here were Chairwoman of the Hyundai Group of south Korea Hyon Jong Un and her party.

U.S. Double Standards in Nuclear Issue Assailed 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 30 (KCNA) -- The chief executive of the United States, taking issue with Iran's nuclear activities, let loose the absurd remark that if Iran forced its nuclear armament, the third world war would break out. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Urging the U.S. to prove in practice its stand against the outbreak of another world war and nuclear proliferation, if it truly stood against them, a Minju Joson analyst Tuesday says: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. calls into question the nuclear activities of "hostile countries" while keeping mum about the nuclear weaponization of its allies. A typical example is its double-dealing act of supporting Israel's nuclear weaponization. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This year the U.S. signed an agreement on cooperation in the nuclear field with a country remaining outside the NPT. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Such double-dealing nuclear policy of the U.S. has given rise to displeasure in the international community and its unfair approach to the issue of nuclear nonproliferation has laid a stumbling block in the worldwide efforts for nuclear disarmament. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. does not pursue a unitary standard and consistency in its nuclear policy. It only abuses it for its strategy to dominate the world. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Not much penetration is needed to see why it called Iran to account again for its nuclear activities, throwing together balderdash about the outbreak of the third world war. The U.S. is examining a military option as a countermeasure in case Iran's nuclear issue would not be solved as it wants. What the U.S. seeks through the spread of the rumor in the international community about Iran's nuclear weaponization and ensuing outbreak of the third world war is to use it as a pretext for a military attack on Iran. The spread of the rumor about the nightmarish third world war in the international community is also aimed to drag passive countries deeper into its intensified sanctions against Iran. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. policy in handling sensitive political issues which require responsibility in a careless manner to meet its own interests is, in fact, pushing the world into a nuclear arms race. This proves that the U.S. is a dangerous nuclear criminal bringing the era of a new nuclear arms race, the cold war which will spark off the third world war.

Rodong Sinmun Calls for Holding Higher Banner of Self-Reliance
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 30 (KCNA) -- Self-reliance serves as the banner of struggle to glorify the 21st century as an era of prosperity of the country and the indomitable spirit of the Korean people valiantly advancing toward a bright future with great ambition, declares Rodong Sinmun Tuesday in a signed article. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Self-reliance is a strategy consistently maintained by the Workers' Party of Korea in the economic construction in the 21st century, the article says, and goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The key to changing the appearance of the DPRK's economy as required by the new century is to strictly apply the principle of self-reliance. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 What is most important for pushing forward socialist construction at present is how to apply the principle of self-reliance in keeping with the changed circumstances. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Self-reliance pursued by the WPK in the 21st century means self-reliance based on science and technology. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The WPK sets it as the basic task of self-reliance to update technology as required by the new century and accelerate the production and construction with one's own efforts on the basis of it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The plan of the WPK to build an economic power is based on the firm conviction that there is nothing impossible in the world when giving full play to the inexhaustible creative power of the scientists and technicians in the DPRK firmly armed with the Songun idea of Juche and possessed of a high degree of scientific and technological qualifications. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Self-reliance called for by the WPK in the 21st century means self-reliance based on profitability. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is the consistent principle of the WPK to plan any work and conduct it in such a manner as to gain substantial profits by giving overriding importance to profitability in all fields ranging from economic and cultural construction to external activities. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Self-reliance serves as an engine reenergizing the independent economy of the DPRK in all fields. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Reenergizing the national economy as required by the WPK does not mean a simple work to restore what used to be in the past but overall technological updating. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is very important for updating the national economy to actively apply ultra-modern science and technology from other countries. It also means self-reliance if one makes world-known ultra-modern technology one's own and actively applies it. The economy in the DPRK is making dynamic progress, being steadily equipped with the advanced technology, because it has maintained such realistic stand in economic construction. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Self-reliance serves as a powerful weapon for resolutely shattering the imperialists' economic blockade. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Unprecedented was the economic pressure against the DPRK by the imperialists in the recent period. The DPRK has been exposed to the enemy's blockade for decades but never have the imperialists applied such harsh and base sanctions against it as now in terms of their scope and strength and method. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The imperialists' moves to isolate and suffocate the DPRK have not only failed but backfired. Signal successes have been reported from various fields of the national economy and more monumental structures built at a time when the situation reached an extreme pitch of tension. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Self-reliance serves as a banner of struggle as it helped firmly maintain the socialist principle in all fields of economic construction. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean people have never abandoned the socialist principle either in the struggle to defend socialism in the past century or in the onward march in the new century. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The advance being made by the Korean people in the spirit of self-reliance is a hope-filled advance as it provides a sure guarantee for their final victory. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They have the strong mental spirit to valiantly pull through any adversity. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This spirit reinforced in the crucible of the protracted revolution grew immensely stronger in the days of defending socialism in the closing years of the past century. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They have the inexhaustible creative power to bring about any epoch-making change. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Underlying their strong mental spirit and creative power are the fixed faith that one is sure to win when following the leader of the revolution and the do-or-die determination to steadfastly make long journeys of revolution, remaining loyal to the leader. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 There is a bright prospect for the Songun revolution thanks to the headquarters of the revolution headed by Kim Jong Il.

Rodong Sinmun on Inevitable Victory of Socialism
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 30 (KCNA) -- Socialism is science and truth and is the most progressive society in human history, says Rodong Sinmun Tuesday in a signed article. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Socialism is making steady victorious progress for its scientific accuracy, truth and validity, the article says, and goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The imperialists and those who speak for them are talking about "failure and end of socialism" while letting loose sheer sophism that the idea of socialism is wrong and it was wrong to start a socialist revolution. But it is imperialism, not socialism that is going to ruin and destruction in actuality. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Socialism represents the desire and wish of the popular masses. This is one of the reasons why it is the historical inevitability for socialism to triumph. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The cause of socialism is a just cause of achieving independence of the popular masses. Socialism reflects their desire and wish to live and develop independently. It also guarantees the independent development of a country and nation. It represents an ideal and future of humankind. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
It is a new society fundamentally different from the preceding societies that served the exploiting class. It is only the socialist society that provides the popular masses with an ample opportunity of realizing independence, their cherished desire. It is inevitable and quite natural for the popular masses to aspire after and demand socialism. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Another reason why socialism is sure to triumph is that it is a law governing the development of history that society based on individualism is sure to be replaced by a society based on collectivism, i.e. by socialism. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The fundamental difference between capitalism and socialism is that the former is based on individualism while the latter is based on collectivism. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The superiority of socialism to capitalism finds its clear manifestation in the political field, above all. This superiority also finds a striking expression in the economic field, too. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is the historical inevitability for socialism to triumph because it is a law governing the development of history that the new is certain to win while the old is bound to go to ruin, concludes the article.

DPRK Bachelor's Degree Conferred on Teacher of Democratic Congo
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 30 (KCNA) -- The DPRK's bachelor's degree of philosophy was awarded to Roland Vele Mukelenge, a teacher of University of Kinshasa in Democratic Congo, in recognition of his great contribution to the dissemination of the Juche idea. He explained that the Juche idea is a great political philosophy. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A ceremony of awarding the degree was held at the Mansudae Assembly Hall on Tuesday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there were Kwak Pom Gi, vice-premier of the Cabinet who is chairman of the State Commission for Conferring Degrees and Titles of the DPRK, Kang Chun Gum, secretary general of the commission, and officials concerned.

Cultural and Emotional Life of Working People in Autumn
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 30 (KCNA) -- Working people are enjoying a diversified cultural and emotional life in scenic spots across the country ushering in autumn. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Taedong and Pothong Rivers flowing through Pyongyang are crowded with anglers and young people and members of the Korean Children's Union who are amusing themselves by boating. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Cultural recreation grounds including Mt. Kuwol, Mt. Jongbang and Ulrim Falls which have been renovated in the Songun era, are all aflame with autumn tints. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The picturesque autumn scenery is attracting the eyes of art fans. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Seen in the parks and recreation grounds in Pyongyang, Kanggye, Hamhung, Sariwon and other parts of the country are working people of various strata who are on a family picnic on Sunday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Old man Kim Tok Bok, 73, told KCNA at the Taesongsan Pleasure Park that it is part of his life to enjoy the holiday along with his family members and relatives. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The holidaymakers are grateful to Kim Jong Il who finds the greatest pleasure in the happy visage of the people and continues the long journey for Songun leadership. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean people are vigorously forging ahead toward the rose morrow of the country, enjoying the emotional life full of labor and rest, struggle and optimism and creation and enjoyment.

Mass Physical Culture and Sports Brisk in DPRK
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 30 (KCNA) -- Physical culture and sports activities have become more brisk among the people of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea in the autumn season. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@All the units throughout the country are holding sports and amusement games in a planned way, which are replete with the optimistic life of the working people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Industrial establishments in Pyongyang including the Kim Jong Thae Electric Locomotive Plant, the Pyongyang Automation Instrument Factory and the Kangdong County Basic Foodstuff Factory are exercising in a regular way the running, mass rhythmic gymnastics and health-promoting Taekwon-Do, thus establishing an atmosphere of sports, cultural and emotional life in the working sites. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Workers of the industrial establishments in North Hamgyong Province including the Kim Chaek Iron and Steel Complex and the Musan Mining Complex are taking an active part in mass sporting activities so as to prepare themselves as "masters of sports".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Those in North Phyongan Province take the breaks and holidays to hold such national sports and folk amusement games as ssirum (Korean wrestling), tug-of-war, swinging, seesaw, chess and yut-game. In this way, they are positively retaining national traditions. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Colorful sports activities of working people and the school youth and children are being held in parks and pleasure grounds across the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@This year has witnessed the sports contest of officials of provincial (city) institutions to commemorate the Day of the Sun, the sports contest of officials of national institutions for Paektusan Cup, the national sports contest of workers, the national ssirum (Korean wrestling) tournament for grand bull prize and others. They fully show the ever-developing mass sports activities.

Moves for Increased Share of Upkeep for U.S. Military Presence Denounced
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 30 (KCNA) -- The People for Achieving Peace and Reunification in south Korea reportedly held a press conference in front of the building of the Ministry of Foreign Affairs and Trade in Seoul on October 24 to denounce the U.S. and south Korean authorities' moves for increasing the share of the upkeep for the U.S. troops present in south Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Speakers at the conference charged that at the U.S.-south Korea discussion on plans for developing the system of defence cost sharing, the U.S. is seeking to force the south Korean side to burden even the fund for the transfer of its military base aimed at realizing its strategy of domination by putting it in the "list of defence cost sharing".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They held that the south Korean authorities should stop the humiliating "discussion" and abrogate the payment of upkeep for the U.S. troops.

Information Bulletin on DPRK Issued in Austria 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 30 (KCNA) -- Information bulletin titled "Down-with-Imperialism Union (DIU) and the Workers' Party of Korea" was released by the Group of Youth for the Study of Kim Jong Il Juche Idea in Vienna, Austria on Oct. 23 on the occasions of the 62nd founding anniversary of the WPK and the 81st anniversary of the formation of the DIU. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The bulletin said that the more than six decade-long history of the WPK is a great history in which it paved a unique way of building a revolutionary party in the era of independence under the banner of the Juche idea, set a world-wide example in socialist construction through the most arduous struggle and recorded a heroic epic of the anti-imperialist struggle. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The glorious road of victory covered by the WPK is closely associated with the immortal history of President Kim Il Sung, it noted. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Today the WPK boasts a large number of its members who are armed with the same spirit of devotedly defending the leader and transparent spirit of independence against imperialism as the members of the DIU cherished, the bulletin noted, adding that the WPK has steadfastly carried forward the tradition of the DIU under the leadership of Kim Jong Il.

Kim Jong Il se reune con Liu Yunshan
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, 30 de octubre (ATCC) -- El Dirigente Kim Jong Il, Secretario General del Partido del Trabajo de Corea y Presidente del Comite de Defensa Nacional de la Republica Popular Democratica de Corea, recibio en audiencia el dia 30 a Liu Yunshan, miembro del Buro Politico y de la Secretaria y jefe del Departamento de Propaganda del Comite Central del Partido Comunista de China, y su comitiva, de visita en Corea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  En la ocasion el visitante transmitio al Dirigente un mensaje oral de Hu Jintao, Secretario General del Comite Central del Partido Comunista de China y por encargo le informo del estado de la efectuacion del XVII congreso del PCCh. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  El Secretario General expreso agradecimiento al respecto, felicito la exitosa realizacion de dicho congreso y departio con el huesped chino en un ambiente cordial y amistoso. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  A continuacion, el Dirigente ofrecio un almuerzo en honor de los huespedes. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  A la comida fueron invitados Liu Yunshan y su comitiva, asi como Liu Xiaoming, embajador extraordinario y plenipotenciario de la Republica Popular China en Corea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Tambien estuvieron presentes el primer vicecanciller Kang Sok Ju, el jefe de departamento del CC del PTC Kim Yang Gon, los subjefes de departamentos del CC del PTC Ji Jae Ryong y Pak Kyong Son. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  El almuerzo transcurrio en un ambiente lleno de sentimiento amistoso. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Ese dia, al Dirigente le dirigio presente Liu Yunshan.

Choe Thae Bok departe con Liu Yunshan
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, 30 de octubre (ATCC) -- Tuvieron lugar la vispera las conversaciones entre Choe Thae Bok, miembro suplente del Buro Politico y secretario del Comite Central del Partido del Trabajo de Corea, y Liu Yunshan, miembro del Buro Politico y de la Secretaria y jefe del Departamento de Propaganda del Comite Central del Partido Comunista de China. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  En la ocasion estuvieron presentes por la parte coreana el subjefe de departamento del CC del PTC Pak Kyong Son y otros funcionarios y, por la china, la comitiva de Liu Yunshan y el embajador Liu Xiaoming. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Las conversaciones transcurrieron en un ambiente camaraderil y amistoso.
